verbose_text: The selective NET inhibitor, nisoxetine (10 muM), completely blocked the inhibition of IPSCs produced by cocaine (99.31% +/- 3.00% of control, n = 7; p < 0.05 versus cocaine, unpaired t test, XREF_FIG), suggesting that cocaine promotes activation of alpha 1 Rs and the mobilization of 2-AG through the inhibition of NET.
